			<description><![CDATA[<p>
The training specialist is responsible for educating tens of thousands of Linode customers. This is a huge opportunity to lead the launch of our new online training program and help our customers learn to use Linux and fully utilize their virtual servers. You&#39;ll identify the best training methods, create curriculum for online courses, script and record videos, and evaluate the effectiveness of our training programs.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Primary Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Manage all training programs &mdash; including online training, customer-facing classes, and internal training and certification courses.</li>
<li>
<p>
Work together with the marketing and documentation teams to launch a comprehensive training video series and create an ongoing education curriculum to boost customer engagement, product usage, and retention.</p>
</li>
<li>
Lead web-based classes and in-person presentations on a variety of subjects.</li>
<li>
<p>
Assist in writing technical blog posts for Linode customers.</p>
</li>
<li>
Ensure that our online training content stays up to date as updates and new features become available.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Job Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
BS/BA with 2+ years of training experience, preferably at a technology company.</li>
<li>
<p>
Strong technology background preferred. Experience with Linux and associated packages such as Apache, PHP, Perl, MySQL, and Postfix is highly desirable, but not required.</p>
</li>
<li>
Demonstrated mastery of instructional design, online training, and evaluation methodologies.</li>
<li>
<p>
Excellent oral, written, and interpersonal skills to clearly communicate and articulate technical information in a non-technical manner.</p>
</li>
<li>
Self-starter with ability to plan and execute work with minimal supervision.</li>
<li>
<p>
Proven creativity and openness to new approaches and emerging change.</p>
</li>
<li>
Experience using popular online training applications such as Captivate, ScreenFlow, and Articulate as well as web-based meeting tools such as WebEx, LiveMeeting, and Go-to-Meeting.</li>
</ul>
